                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003 C 73/228: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-12-17T15:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 17, 1925—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 17—9:09 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>532. Opening of Extraterritoriality Commission which should take place tomorrow
                    will be delayed until arrival of Belgian, British, <pb facs="1016" n="890"
                        xml:id="pg_890"/> French and Italian Commissioners who are detained at
                    Tientsin by the interruption of all means of communication in consequence of
                    factional fighting now in progress. In spite of Chief Executive’s orders to both
                    parties to facilitate arrangements for the operation of an international train
                    it has not yet been possible to effectuate such an arrangement with Marshall
                    Feng’s commander here. Repeated to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
